      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial constitutional tool that protects fundamental rights against government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon deeply held liberties even if it follows proper procedures. This doctrine has been instrumental in expanding civil rights, notably by protecting privacy and bodily autonomy against legislative intrusion. It serves as a vital check on government power, safeguarding the individual against tyranny.",
